newItemDescription: Philippine Jasmine or Sampaguita, scientifically known as Jasminum sambac, is an exquisite and highly fragrant flowering plant that is native to the Philippines. With its delicate white flowers and sweet floral scent, it adds a touch of elegance and sensory delight to any garden or landscape. Philippine Jasmine thrives in full sun to partial shade and prefers well-drained soil. It is a popular choice for gardens, especially in tropical and subtropical regions, where its charming blooms and intoxicating fragrance create a serene and captivating atmosphere.
